<div><h3>ECON 2240 - Introductory Game Theory </h3>  <hr>This course introduces the basic concepts of game theory, which has become a fundamental tool in not only social science disciplines such as economics or political science but also other emerging disciplines such as biology and data science. The goals of this course are to introduce students to the framework of game theory and strategic thinking, to identify real-world questions that could be answered by game theory, and eventually, to shed some light in applying game theory to critically analyze and predict political, economic and algorithmic problems in today&#8217;s world.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> 201905<br><br></div>		</td>
